                            <comment id="17248428" author="msahyoun" created="Sat, 12 Dec 2020 18:36:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Reason was two fold&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a) we don&apos;t support PaperMetaData barcode generation&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;b) for the PaperMetaData there was a text containing a lot of spaces which has been treated as a single word. Trimming that before the substring is wrong (at least with our current implementation)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17248430" author="msahyoun" created="Sat, 12 Dec 2020 18:37:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; I don&apos;t know how you came across the issue. Maybe you can test the fix. I&apos;ll close afterwards.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17248449" author="tilman" created="Sat, 12 Dec 2020 20:03:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, works fine (there is a typo &quot;widet&quot;). I came across the issue in the regression tests. Before the fix, I could reproduce it with PDFDebugger, in the View Menu, select &quot;repair acroform&quot;, but now it works.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
